The paper deals with knowledge graphs and their completion using embedding models, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of training objectives to improve performance, which is a common topic in database systems (cs.DB) and information retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the paper deals with natural language processing tasks such as answering compositional questions, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL).
